HEADWORD: Roccellin
<hw>Roc*cel"lin</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A red dyestuff,
used as a substitute for cochineal, archil, etc. It consists of the
sodium salt of a complex azo derivative of naphtol.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Roche</ent>⟦br⟧
